  <datafield tag="545" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Public affairs and communications unit within the University Housing administration responsible for disseminating information and serving as spokesman for student housing related issues. Alan Levy served as Housing Public Affairs director beginning in the 1990s, but performed similar functions earlier.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Topical files and reports on various campus issues and controversies, particularly as they involved housing. Topics include affirmative action, alcohol poicies, crime, diversity, housing rates, and national and international events such as the Virginia Tech massacre, Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS), and 9-11 terrorist attacks. Also includes files on Nu Sigma Nu and the purchase of the fraternity house to the University. The files were collected and created by Alan Levy who served numerous roles in housing in addition to public affairs.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="506" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
